  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthen Health Emergency Response by Supporting Post Trauma Physical Rehabilitation and WASH Services to PWDs Living in Conflict Affected Areas</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to protect conflict-affected, underserved, and natural disaster-affected people with disabilities from negative consequences in Afghanistan. This WHO project provides post trauma physical rehabilitation services, psychosocial support training for health workers, hand-pumps for PWDs and rehabilites toilets designed for PwDs among other activities. The project provides life-saving assistance to 7,500 people, including 1,500 women, 5,250 men, 700 children, and 7,500 persons with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
